<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6f1b2fb-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57304"><num value="57304">§ 57304.</num><heading> Eligible acquisition dates</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">At the option of the owner, the acquisition of an obsolete vessel under this chapter shall occur—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6f1b2fc-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57304/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> when the owner contracts for the construction or purchase of a new vessel; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6f1b2fd-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57304/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> within 5 days of the actual date of delivery of the new vessel to the owner.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf6f1b2fe-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1662">120 Stat. 1662</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
